.SH "SYNOPSIS"
Here you will find information on how to login \'Dalma\'\.
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If you are outside NYU campus, connect to NYU VPN as instructed here \fIhttp://www\.nyu\.edu/life/resources\-and\-services/information\-technology/getting\-started/network\-and\-connectivity/vpn\.html\fR first\.
.
.SS "MAC / LINUX"
For Linux / Mac, execute the following command\. Change username to your actual username\.
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

ssh username@dalma\.abudhabi\.nyu\.edu
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.SS "WINDOWS"
We recommend Putty as your ssh client\. It is available for download here \fIhttp://www\.chiark\.greenend\.org\.uk/~sgtatham/putty/download\.html\fR\.
.
.P
1\.\- (First\-time login only) Setup Butinah session in your putty\.
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

\- Open Putty\. Go to Category \-> Session\.
\- Type dalma\.abudhabi\.nyu\.edu in Host Name (or IP address)\.
\- Type Dalma under Saved Sessions\.
\- Click Save button\. A new session called Dalma will appear in Saved Sessions\.
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
2\.\- Select Dalma session\. Click Load button\.
.
.P
3\.\- Click Open button\.
.
